He thought me dangerous with Hermann , more than with the girl herself but , as to quarrelling , I saw at once how inappropriate the word was . 
Natural forces are not quarrelsome . 
You can't quarrel with the wind that inconveniences and humiliates you by blowing off your hat in a street full of people . 
He had no quarrel with me . 
Neither would a boulder , falling on my head , have had . 
He fell upon me in accordance with the law by which he was moved not of gravitation , like a detached stone , but of self preservation . 
Of course this is giving it a rather wide interpretation . 
